    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <head>No. 208.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-02-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 5, 1887</date>.
                            (Received March 31.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 58.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Previous dispatches from this legation have
                        informed the Department, of the opening in Seoul, by a number of American
                        missionaries, of schools, an orphanage, a hospital, and of other useful
                        undertakings due to them. In all these they have received the hearty support
                        of this legation.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
